Chat GPT generated note for audio:

Audio Note: This stream is recorded with two separate microphones going to left/right channels because my camera (Sony HXR-NX800) and streaming encoder (LiveU Solo PRO) don't support mono mixing. This means you'll hear one person in your left ear and the other in your right ear.
If this bothers you, you can enable mono audio on your device:
iPhone/iPad: Settings → Accessibility → Audio/Visual → toggle on "Mono Audio"
Android: Settings → Accessibility → Hearing → toggle on "Mono audio" (exact path varies by manufacturer)
There's actually a small benefit to this setup - if both people talk over each other, you can mentally tune into whichever conversation you want to follow. But I get it, it's not ideal for most people.
The edited version of this video will have proper mono audio so both voices come through both ears normally. For now, the raw stream is what it is
